Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
lefIgnoreLayerNames(25.10)                          lefIgnoreLayerNames(25.10)

Name
       lefIgnoreLayerNames

Syntax
        lefIgnoreLayerNames <layerNames>

       Type: String

       Default: NULL

       Specifies  the layer list that needs to be ignored. If you do not spec-
       ify any layers in this global, the tool load all layers.  For  example,
       if  you specify lefIgnoreLayerNames "TSV BSPM0", the tool will not load
       the definition for the TSV layer and BSPM0 layer when loading the  tech
       LEF  file.  You  should  use this global to disable the layer list when
       loading an OA design.

       If the disabled layers are used in the Tech LEF for via cell, via  rule
       generation, NDR and property definition, the tool will ignore the defi-
       nition  when loading the Tech LEF file. If the disables layers are used
       in macro LEF, tool will stop reading the LEF file and give an error. If
       the disabled layers are used in the definition of the following objects
       in other design data, the tool will give error to skip this object:

                     * Wire/Via

                     * Marco Pin/OBS (Include bump)

                     * Blockage

                     * Bus guide

                     * Track

                     * Pin guide

                     * GUI shape/text

                     * Pin guide

